node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Italy • Travel • Passion in Ponte Vecchio. May be an image of the Arno River.

node.text:
▪ The Ponte Vecchio is a medieval stone closed-spandrel segmental arch bridge over the Arno River, in Florence, Italy. It is noted for the shops built along it, as was once common. Butchers, tanners, and farmers initially occupied the shops; the present tenants are jewelers, art dealers, and souvenir sellers.⁣

Photo by Italy • Travel • Passion in Tellaro. May be an image of coast, nature, ocean and sky.

node.text:
▪ When you first get to Tellaro (considered by Italian experts to be one of Italy's loveliest towns) you'll find it is a maze of tiny little lanes and passageways that simply tempt one to explore.⁣
⁣
Go and get lost! 😍⁣
⁣
With Tellaro being so small you'll not be lost for long and you'll soon find yourself back in the piazza or down by the little harbor.⁣
⁣
After a few days, you'll know and love every nook and cranny. 😄⁣
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••⁣
